rComments: I don't agree with the bad reviews, I would recommend this prof to anyone. Exams are easy and sometimes even sitcom themed, he makes funny references in his lectures and answers all questions clearly. The midterm paper was also super easy and actually graded you for comprehension of the topic. Definitely take this prof.

All of these bad reviews are from people who put no effort into the class, don't listen to them. I've taken this prof twice and his midterms are SO EASY if you listen to the lectures. That is all. He literally gives the answers to everything in his lectures. Textbook not required, exams are MCQ and really short. Hes really sweet and overall amazing
if you want a professor who vents about his shortcomings as a researcher in a class teaching research methods he's your man. Terrible experience having him as a professor.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'So many papers', 'Tough grader']

rComments: Not accessible outside class AT ALL!! Exams are hard too. Good luck with that if you have to take this class!! The prof is nice though

Dr Durand's lectures are very clear, straightforward and easy to understand. While he can be a bit dry, he applies the course material to real situations in statistics and research. Dr Durand is very relatable and honest. His exams follow the course content exactly. Take statistics with him, he's very cool.

Powerpoints are unclear and the french translation is sometimes off. Lectures are not engaging whatsoever. No practice or any application other than the lab, but it is a light course and decently easy to understand.
Such a chill prof, I liked his online program.

I understand that following the rules of conduct are important, but being a professor also entails a proper level of empathy and compassion, which Professor Durand lacked. I explained my tour situation and asked for an extension, and he flat out sent an email saying "NO." which I found very offensive and unprofessional.

He's a good prof and tries his best to make the class interesting especially since it's online. There are two midterms, one paper and the option to either write a second paper or final exam. Exams are multiple choice and fair/reflect course material however some questions can only be found in the textbook (can be found free online)

Professor Durand is amazing! He answers emails pretty quickly, and answers questions in class clearly, making sure you understand. He's extremely accommodating when it comes to the exam and the assignment given. Psychometrics is a really boring course and can be quite complicated at times, and he made sure everyone could understand!

Great teacher, I would recommend him 100%. exams reflect class material exactly so if you pay attention and takes notes you'll pass. He's also funny and not boring to listen to. Would take the class again!

Listen, he's the least bad of Psychometric teachers. If you have no other options, just take him. All he does really is read from his powerpoint. He isn't mean or anything, just not interesting. He's very strict with grade changes, and test are MC
He's realy and helpfull. The only thing is that he's fast, but if you ask, he will reexplain for you! Realy human

honestly don't know why his reviews are so bad, I took psychopathology with him during the spring-summer term and loved having him as a prof. The class was asynchronous so could be watched on your own time and sped up. 2 multiple choice exams and 2 case studies, he also gives practice exams and practice case studies so you know what to expect!
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: This class is boring! I didn't find him awful as a prof but not great either. The exams are pretty easy, but the papers are SO much work! Grading entirely depends on the TA you get, my first paper sucked & I got 100 but my 2nd was so much better & I got an 80 (not bad but not reflective of my effort or quality especially compared to the first one)

Psychometric Methods as a course is -so- boring, but Guillaume isn't to blame for that. His lectures are comprehensive (you will not pass exams without listening to the lectures) and asynchronous, so they can be sped up. Posts practice questions, sample assignments, and the exams are easy if you read the slides and listen to the lectures. Good Prof

He is kind of dull, but you really have to pay attention to what he says in his lectures, not just concepts on the slides. Theres 2 papers 2 mini quizzes and an optional final for people who got over 80%. I thought the grading was fair but its not the most thrilling class.
Funny thing!!!! One day he was a high school teacher! The guy is just okay! He dont care about nothing but himself. However, he is fair. Just study and you will get the marks.

I love the way he structured his class! We had mini quizzes, papers, and a final but not mandatory if you got above 80% which was AWESOME! He answers emails really quickly, he gives amazing examples in class, fair grader and fair questions. He really made me enjoy psychometrics! Would def take again :)

He made psychometrics such an enjoyable and fun class. Gives many concrete examples and makes the topics interesting. Asynchronous lectures which was greatly appreciated. Gives hints and concrete question examples at the DGDs. The 2 assignments are definetely tough and long to do. Very fair quiz questions. Answers emails very quickly. Great prof.

Such a funny guy. Made boring content into something I will actually remember learning. Have to go to lecture to do well on exams, they are 50/50 on slides + what's said in class. Had 3 midterms + 2 assignments and a final. Final was optional if you get over 80% in course content - first time he did this. Overall, awesome guy and made it enjoyable

Prof Durand is a nice guy, sarcastic in lectures and really tries his best to be interesting in class. But his assignment workload is insane - ran me into the ground trying to finish it in time. Take this prof if you're good at writing papers. Also read the textbook because a lot of his test questions are from there
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'So many papers', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Dr. Durand is a good professor, but he has a tendency to run topics into the ground. Really great when you don't understand a concept as he gives lots of examples, but can be boring when material is simple to grasp. I've had him for research methods and psychometrics. Exams can be very tough. Show up/watch every lecture or you WILL miss things!
he's amazing! very fair grader and very empathetic. he answers his emails immediately

Prof. Durand is a great guy. He doesn't try to trick you or make things unnecessarily complicated. He's funny in a sarcastic way and makes a dry class interesting. Take good notes, attend the dgd's, and study and you'll get a good grade. As a newer, younger prof, he gets the struggles of being a student and acknowledges them. Take his class!
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Gives good feedback', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: He makes class interesting, he is quite funny and very sarcastic. If you pay attention and write detailed notes during lectures you should get a good grade.

Professor Durand is very clear with his explanations and makes the content easy to understand so long as you participate in lectures. Most of my class did poorly on tests, but I don't think this is Professor Durand's fault, as I actually found the tests very easy. He was also very helpful when reviewing my research rough draft!

I was pleasantly surprised given his past reviews. Dr Durand conveyed the material well, and his lectures were fun. His real life clinical case examples brought a lot to the course. He was happy to answer any questions during DGD's and gave clear explanations. 2 small case studies with clear marking scheme. Gave practice midterm/final too.

Super nice prof. His classes are very interesting especially because he gives a lot of real life examples on clinical psych. It was always fun to listen to his class online. He's an excellent prof and he focus on the big picture not the small little details in the psychopathology textbook that everyone forgets after the exams.

Reading the past reviews, I was kinda worried when I started that class. The class turned out great. The weekly online quizzes were REALLY helpful. He was clearly putting a lot of effort to be as interesting as possible. Overall the class was pretty easy.

DO NOT TAKE HIS CLASS! His midterm average was very low and he didnt even bother showing up to it. He is extremely tough on marking, gives vague instruction, and honestly just doesnt know how to conduct a class. Absolutely the worst professor Ive ever had. Get ready to learn ONLY about psychopathy because thats all he fully understands.

By far the worst teacher I've ever had. Very arrogant, doesn't care about his students, he blames the class when everyone does bad on his midterm that made no sense and mocks us for it as well. Didn't even show up to the midterm, the only reason that I did okay was because of the labs worth 25%.

Honestly, he seems like a nice guy. But his self-esteem was really shook when people stopped showing up to his classes. Because of his low self-esteem, it was really hard to not want to skip his class. His attitude and body language made it seem like he was looking for a pity party. The midterm was hard and he was upset about about the low average

As many others have said he is very knowledgeable and understands what he is teaching very well but he is unable to convey that message to the class effectively. The labs save your grade as they are writing exercises related to the research portion of the course which are not hard to complete.

Nice person, but an extremely hard marker. I attended all classes and still (like majority of the class) did not do well on his midterm. His teaching style isn't bad but the way he writes him midterms makes it difficult to do well.

I highly don't recommend this prof. He is clearly very smart and understands what he is talking about. However, that doesn't mean he is a good prof. He is boring because all he does is overexplain and reads off slides. I also find it weird how he often jokes about his self-esteem, it makes me pity him and feel bad in the class. 2/10 Avoid.
reads off of his slides and adds basically nothing. boring content, boring prof. srry he seems like a nice guy but not a v good prof

really nice guy, however english is his third language and its very hard to understand him. his lectures are very dry and boring, midterms were very difficult pretty sure the whole class did bad. he reads off his slides and doesn't add very much, also he gave us the text book which was nice too bad his lectures were a copy and paste of it.
